IF I AM AN ARTIST,
DO I STILL DO NOT KNOW

ABOUT THE COMPOSER FRANK HOLGER ROTHKAMM, UNCONVENTIONAL OPUS COUNTING AND ELECTRONIC MUSIC

by Klaus Huebner



501 works with a total playing time of 55 hours, 59 minutes and one second (as of 20 May 2013): Frank Holger Rothkamm's output offers a wide ranging sound empire that he during his time as an actor at the Palace Theatre in the Lower Rhine Moers word from developed and staged reality. Was similar to Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart stopped by his father, Leopold, to be numbered among his works, and served
its directory of all my works the composer Rothkamm as a pattern to create a separate directory in the age of MP3 technology and the resulting need quantification of the works.

Rothkamm began in 2002, after he had completed by an inner enlightenment a radical change to the past as an artist and this is also documented externally through a total head hair shaving to komponieren.Von intuitive music to psychedelic based this time on "counted" He his works: When Opus 1 is the piece of Earth Frequency Synthesizer
Oscillator called, which was re-released on CD with the FB01 developed by the composers' IFORMM "system. The opus numbers are identical with the serial numbers of a database in which Rothkamm his work has captured. As more music from Roth comb
oldest past turns up, the ever-increasing catalog of works. Previously, Roth comb conserved musical traces back to the year 1982 can be traced.

Franz Holger Rothkamm coincides with his (musical) Biography of the frame: he began as an actor, as someone who has foreign texts and uses foreign characters, his own ego of the respective subordinate role. Without a doubt, this is a creative, strange as the base springs-use performance. Roth Biography rugged ridge showed at an early age cracking, splitting and restlessness, uncomfortable and sometimes life-inflammatory side effects that his musical creativity increasingly certain. Against this background, his work, embedded in computerized and electronic music as well as performative actions as a way to form, as a synthesis of sound art and popular musical forms and styles. Appears Red comb electronic works are in contact with the works of serial music of Karlheinz Stockhausen, Herbert Eimert or Franco Evangelisti from the 1950s - electronic sound sequences in the field of tension between tradition and experiment. How analogously developed in Rothkamm to Beuys' expanded concept of art, an extended concept of music, he demonstrates ALT: microtonal, droneartige Ambientflitter, wrapped in embossed linear frequency patterns.

MOERS - BERLIN - AMERICA

Frank Holger Rothkamm was born in 1965 in Gutersloh, the hometown of Hans Werner Henze. There he received his first piano lessons and was interested in drawing. At the age of twelve years, he lived with his family in Nuertingen (Baden-Württemberg) - created his first compositions. Music grasp - that was for the young Frank Holger Rothkamm a passion. "Music frees us from Akademismen and conventions. The music must be met with the same curiosity and surprise like how the manifestations of nature, "
Hans Werner Henze wrote in the preface, edited by Franz Xaver Ohnesorg book The Liberation of Music (1994). After Rothkamm had a string quartet by Paul Hindemith heard on the radio were revealed to him the desire and curiosity and surprise led to a new understanding of music. He constructed an own graphical notation for a composition for two pianos, which he "youth composes" the competition submitted. His work was rejected because the jury did not consider it music. They corresponded so exactly the opposite of Henze's postulate. Rothkamm sat acoustic tracks - first on cassette, as with the several sequels experiencing FISH series, which started with a performance on Crete.

1980 continued Rothkamm Moers piano at the music school training and continued learning violin. About his music teacher Karl Heinz Witte, he established contacts with the avant-garde oriented local Castle Theatre. Reproduction prohibited for production developed Rothkamm a piano piece and used it a few quotes from Anton Bruckner's seventh symphony. Another move took him to Cologne in 1985, where he performed community service at the University Hospital. He worked extensively with algorithms for computer music and published on this
Based sculptures after the album Music (1986), which made its debut as a recording artist
and marked with the same time he took leave from the acoustic piano. The 1984 by Ingo Graebner and Andrea Buchwald as free artist initiative and venue with differentiated
Work opportunities for action based artist and creator of spatial works Sommering studio in Cologne was the ideal place for the composer and conceptual artist Rothkamm.
There he led in 1985 to the music performance Tien, a "powerful" with synthesizer sounds
and violin passages designed Dekonstruktionshappening: With a black hammer he smashed into a darkened room white stone slabs, two monitors emit light, gra-
reduced fish pattern comment, monotonous sound material.

In Berlin Rothkamm studied communication sciences, bionics and philosophy and then went for personal reasons and "the better sex following» to Vancouver, where he
worked with artists and concept for a computer game company. But Vancouver was just a stopover on the way to the U.S., in which he immigrated in 1990. First, he lived in San Francisco, brought out there his first 12'' vinyl record Magick Sounds Of The Underground, as well as the CD Death Rave, 2000. "Why did I go to America, I'm not sure. And I do not understand myself why I did when I bought during that time until about 2008, the house in Los Angeles and founded the utopian <Loge for Wissenschaft>,'ve moved every year, "says Rothkamm. 1994 in New York, he fell ill with depression, suffered from panic-anxiety disorders and depersonalization, which lasted until the previous year.

The unsteady, ten years of commuters living between New York and Los Angeles, accompanied by the establishment of the label Flux Records and the composing of 93 piano pieces with his beloved "Kurzweil K2000» synthesizer Rothkamm supplemented by commercial contracts for
Video Games and soundtracks for film trailers. In addition, he produced remixes for artists such as Elliott Sharp, Alfred 23 Harth undWolfgang Muthspiel music developed concepts for Rodney Graham, Harald Fuchs and DJ Glove and mixed audio from The Cranberries, Zeena Parkins
Rebekka Bakken and new. True to its motto that art and advertising are not intended to exclude, he produced "commercials" for Levi Strauss, Sears and Philips. Besides created soundtracks for experiments with 3-D projection technology, for example Star Wars by George Lucas.

MEDIUM FOR OTHER RESOURCES

A built in 1935 and renovated in 2010 Rothkamm Steinkamp house in Los
Angeles serves the artist as a research center for "psychosis-stochastic Sciences
». A collection of early digital synthesizer, user manuals, vinyl records and various printed materials filled rooms. In Europe, says Rothkamm to stop him from separating
of theory and practice, for example between sound engineer and composer, working to establish multi-functional sound art. Just as he did not like the division between "high" art and popular music, or between the art of Joseph Beuys and advertising continue to follow. True to the Shakespearean motto, "All the world's a stage" is Rothkamm in his performances that you've learned in Moers Castle theater actor a craft: "I
still sit like this a broader idea of ??theater that also <Living Theatre> pursued. After my illness I am working again reinforced with the style means of performance. Since the coming in Moers learned very well to "The Artist as Medium -. Rothkamm sets new standards that have to do with Plato's philosophy reminder, the anamnesis, as with the production of new material from the pen of the composer. "I open myself as a medium for
other beings. »A vehicle for this kind of meditative creativity is discovered by Rothkamm in New York Gabler wing from the year 1922. Ernst Gabler, a German immigrant, who built four very good quality pianos to 1931, constructed a "grand piano" with a warm,
deep and intimate sound that sounds like "Golden Age." Rothkamm discovered - on its own piano training reminiscent - in Carl Czerny etudes and its School of Velocity, the point of attachment to exploit the idea of ??an artist's medium. With Tetralogy he returned, following the Platonic philosophy reminder, back to the classic acoustic piano.

"Whether it is to take my contribution to American or German culture in general, the term art or artists, I do not know. However, what remains - in the sense of the extended concept of art from Beuys - are the products of artistic activity, although
it may be that they are not perceived by future generations. "Knowing that the role of the artist in America is little, Rothkamm found there before the mood, the food is his musical ideas. Even if the reality in
Disasters dissolves. As it happened in 2007, when the "K2000" and historic Studio Equipment victims of the devastating forest fires in California were series. ?



1 Unless otherwise noted, the quotes are from
an interview with Frank Holger Rothkamm of 12 April
, 2013.


